<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4933.1.4>
    bibo:endPage "112" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2021-02-18" ;
    bibo:startPage "98" ;
    bibo:volume "4933" ;
    dc:creator "Zawadzki, Cláudio H.; Nardi, Gabriela; Tencatt, Luiz Fernando Caserta" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "The crystalline waters of the Bodoquena Plateau revealed Hypostomus froehlichi (Siluriformes: Loricariidae), a new armored catfish from the rio Paraguay basin in Brazil" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548036>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548028>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548026>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548030>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548032>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548034> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548036>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Hypostomus froehlichi (a) LIRP 5228, 163.1 mm SL; (b) NUP 12140, 241.8 mm SL, showing tooth variation in specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548036/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548028>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Live specimen of Hypostomus froehlichi, ZUFMS 3606, 188.0 mm SL, Brazil, Mato Grosso do Sul State, córrego Taquaral, rio Paraguay basin, showing general color pattern in lateral view. Photo by Francisco Severo Neto." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548028/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548026>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Hypostomus froehlichi, NUP 22689, 226.2 mm SL, holotype, Brazil, Mato Grosso do Sul State, municipality of Bodoquena, córrego Salobrinha, tributary of rio Miranda, rio Paraguay basin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548026/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548030>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Uncatalogued live specimens of Hypostomus froehlichi in natural habitat, showing juvenile specimens, with (a) 30.0 mm TL and (b) 50.0 mm TL, foraging on rock formations of waterfalls, both in the rio Formoso. Larger specimens, (c) with around 120.0 mm TL, from the rio Formoso, and (d), with around 200.0 mm TL, from the rio da Prata, were often found hiding under rocks and driftwood. Photos (a) and (b) by Peter Petersen, and (c) and (d) by Marcelo Krause." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548030/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548032>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Uncatalogued live specimens of Hypostomus froehlichi in natural habitat, showing (a) a solitary large adult from the rio Mimoso, and (b) part of shoal of large adults from the rio da Prata, both associated with rock formations, where they feed scraping the substrate, leaving feeding scars in the areas in which the periphytic matrix was removed (c). Specimens in (a) and (b) were estimated to have about 400.0 mm TL. Photo (a) by Marcelo Krause, and (b) and (c) by Peter Petersen." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548032/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4548034>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Geographic distribution of Hypostomus froehlichi; (red star = type-locality; white circles = additional records)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4548034/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

